summary:
I am security professional with a diverse experience in intelligence, corporate security, military, training and culture awareness.A highly qualified manager in areas of security management, corporate security, loss prevention, gathering intelligence, security analysis, political analysis, assets protection and investigation. Completed my service in Jordan Army at the rank of lieutenant colonel commanded several posts in the intelligence and security organizations covering areas in terrorism and force protection, geopolitics, providing advice to high levels of leadership including government and Army , coordinating security operations with other local security agencies.
I have an experience with the UN in Georgia where I worked a military information analyst, in charge of presenting the assessments to the senior UN personnel regarding the political and security conditions in the country.

During my career I gained a deep experience in the Middle East and North Africa, I have a full understanding of the security situation in the both region and excellent knowledge of MENA politics and other factors affecting the regions including security threats, political instability and key figures in the region, 
I have the Ability to effectively communicate (oral and written in both Arabic and English) with basic French skills, within all levels of the organization, a Good drafting and presentation skills.

I obtained my master degree in security studies from the national defense University in USA, with another degree in irregular warfare from the United States war college.
As a manager I have a solid experience in HR, Finance, logistic , purchasing for my company, considering the nature of the business, laws, budget, P&L and other factors affecting the daily 

Specialties: counter terroism
